<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The T-shaped hairs are difficult to observe but are distinctive. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="malpighipila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea malpighipila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually easily identified by the terminal inflorescence and obscurely pubescent, trifid leaves with narrowly oblong lobes.
</paragraph>
